pros:
Really busy and fast-paced place so never gets boring;
Good night rate pay;
Easy to book holidays and they are really flexible with rotas;
10% staff discount and at least one double discount event towards the end of the year

cons:
Management team poorly trained and aren't strong when facing their team;
Managers allow childish behaviours and lack on social management skills;
On the shop floor you are allowed a little bit too much freedom so everyone work things their own way which means sometimes people end up wasting time undoing and redoing things;
Managers treat people differently, people let their friendships at work get on the way;
Night team gets forgotten often, even though they run around and work so short staffed, while day team gets rewarded for everything and anything;
Career opportunities only if you are going to work like a slave OR do nothing because you have got "friends" at work / corrupted environment
